1
00:01:09,780 --> 00:01:13,500
=Inherently Kind=

2
00:01:14,740 --> 00:01:17,700
=Episode 20=
(The Comeback)

3
00:01:18,079 --> 00:01:18,640
Nonsense!

4
00:01:19,400 --> 00:01:20,599
Don't you know

5
00:01:20,719 --> 00:01:21,480
who should be the real wife?

6
00:01:22,519 --> 00:01:22,959
Dad.

7
00:01:23,519 --> 00:01:24,799
I have no feelings for Gu Qingmei.

8
00:01:24,840 --> 00:01:26,000
Su Li is the one I like.

9
00:01:26,519 --> 00:01:27,719
Since they look identical,

10
00:01:27,879 --> 00:01:28,640
why can't I choose

11
00:01:28,760 --> 00:01:30,120
the one I like as my wife?

12
00:01:30,640 --> 00:01:32,359
You'd better get a grip.

13
00:01:33,760 --> 00:01:35,079
Does love pay the bills?

14
00:01:35,680 --> 00:01:36,719
The resort acquisition,

15
00:01:36,959 --> 00:01:37,879
the shares,

16
00:01:38,079 --> 00:01:40,719
do they matter less than your love?

17
00:01:43,599 --> 00:01:44,879
Think about Su Li's personality

18
00:01:45,480 --> 00:01:46,879
and Gu Qingmei's personality,

19
00:01:47,079 --> 00:01:48,319
who is easier to control?

20
00:01:48,480 --> 00:01:49,760
Don't you know the answer?

21
00:01:57,840 --> 00:01:59,159
Gu Qingmei has already signed it.

22
00:01:59,599 --> 00:02:01,079
The resort has been secured.

23
00:02:01,580 --> 00:02:03,100
(Yunhu Resort Acquisition Contract)

24
00:02:04,400 --> 00:02:06,000
From now on, she will stay home.

25
00:02:07,280 --> 00:02:08,159
As for Gu Corporation,

26
00:02:08,800 --> 00:02:09,919
you will take charge on her behalf.

27
00:02:11,360 --> 00:02:11,960
Understood?

28
00:02:14,400 --> 00:02:15,840
You'd better not disappoint me.

29
00:02:21,000 --> 00:02:21,560
Xiaoling.

30
00:02:22,039 --> 00:02:23,360
Get me a glass of red wine.

31
00:02:24,520 --> 00:02:25,400
I'm sorry, Madam Gu.

32
00:02:25,680 --> 00:02:26,719
We're out of red wine.

33
00:02:28,520 --> 00:02:29,400
What are you dawdling for?

34
00:02:29,599 --> 00:02:30,719
Get in the kitchen and help.

35
00:02:35,080 --> 00:02:36,719
You still have the nerve
to act high and mighty?

36
00:02:37,000 --> 00:02:37,520
Mom.

37
00:02:37,719 --> 00:02:39,599
I'm the true heir of Gu Corporation.

38
00:02:39,840 --> 00:02:41,400
Why do they disrespect me?

39
00:02:41,719 --> 00:02:42,719
The heir?

40
00:02:44,120 --> 00:02:45,199
If you hadn't been so foolish

41
00:02:45,360 --> 00:02:46,400
to hide abroad

42
00:02:46,759 --> 00:02:48,840
and let an imposter stir up trouble,

43
00:02:49,159 --> 00:02:51,680
Jinchuan wouldn't
have ended up like this.

44
00:02:57,000 --> 00:02:58,759
Why does everyone treat me like this?

45
00:02:59,280 --> 00:03:00,319
Stop crying!

46
00:03:00,759 --> 00:03:01,960
If you can't even
take a little grievance,

47
00:03:02,360 --> 00:03:03,280
how will you manage Gu Corporation?

48
00:03:11,439 --> 00:03:12,039
Qingmei.

49
00:03:13,080 --> 00:03:13,960
It's good to have you back.

50
00:03:14,439 --> 00:03:15,000
Take it slow.

51
00:03:15,680 --> 00:03:16,120
Dad.

52
00:03:17,000 --> 00:03:17,879
In this family,

53
00:03:18,520 --> 00:03:20,680
you're the only one who really cares.

54
00:03:43,960 --> 00:03:44,800
Finally home.

55
00:03:48,840 --> 00:03:50,840
Looks like we've got a household fairy.

56
00:03:52,520 --> 00:03:53,199
Welcome home,

57
00:03:53,879 --> 00:03:54,560
Miss Su.

58
00:03:57,120 --> 00:03:58,319
So that's why you asked for my key,

59
00:03:58,639 --> 00:03:59,639
to surprise me?

60
00:04:00,159 --> 00:04:00,919
Let me help you.

61
00:04:08,520 --> 00:04:09,240
You said

62
00:04:10,400 --> 00:04:11,479
since your parents passed away,

63
00:04:12,479 --> 00:04:14,080
you've been living here alone.

64
00:04:15,319 --> 00:04:15,919
From now on,

65
00:04:16,480 --> 00:04:17,279
I'll be here with you.

66
00:04:20,680 --> 00:04:21,399
You're so sweet.

67
00:04:23,079 --> 00:04:24,600
Once everything is over,

68
00:04:25,839 --> 00:04:27,040
we'll be together forever.

69
00:04:30,800 --> 00:04:32,199
I never expected

70
00:04:32,600 --> 00:04:34,519
a spoiled rich kid like you

71
00:04:34,639 --> 00:04:35,959
to have such cooking skills.

72
00:04:36,279 --> 00:04:38,399
To be honest, life abroad

73
00:04:39,639 --> 00:04:40,720
wasn't as easy as you think.

74
00:04:42,800 --> 00:04:44,319
To fight against the He family,

75
00:04:44,759 --> 00:04:45,639
I've done all sorts of things.

76
00:04:46,199 --> 00:04:47,560
I'll always be by your side from now on.

77
00:04:49,639 --> 00:04:50,879
What's your next move?

78
00:04:52,079 --> 00:04:53,079
Next,

79
00:04:53,839 --> 00:04:54,720
I'm going back to the newspaper.

80
00:04:55,399 --> 00:04:57,120
I'll continue investigating
as a journalist.

81
00:04:58,680 --> 00:04:59,160
Okay.

82
00:05:00,079 --> 00:05:01,120
If you need my help,

83
00:05:01,639 --> 00:05:02,399
just tell me.

84
00:05:03,759 --> 00:05:05,040
What could you do to help?

85
00:05:05,800 --> 00:05:06,439
You

86
00:05:06,480 --> 00:05:09,319
should focus on
being He Jinxi's fiancé for now.

87
00:05:10,879 --> 00:05:13,360
I think I smell jealousy.

88
00:05:13,720 --> 00:05:14,279
Really?

89
00:05:15,160 --> 00:05:17,920
Maybe the neighbors are
making sweet and sour fish.

90
00:05:18,879 --> 00:05:19,720
Then I want to have a try too.

91
00:05:29,240 --> 00:05:29,759
Cheers.

92
00:05:41,879 --> 00:05:42,600
What's going on?

93
00:05:43,720 --> 00:05:45,360
Su Li, you're back!

94
00:05:46,199 --> 00:05:47,519
I told them you'd definitely come back.

95
00:05:47,600 --> 00:05:48,480
No, this is...

96
00:05:48,879 --> 00:05:49,600
Xiao Li!

97
00:05:49,680 --> 00:05:50,600
You're back!

98
00:05:52,399 --> 00:05:54,480
You've been missing for months.

99
00:05:54,800 --> 00:05:56,560
Do you treat the newspaper
as your personal playground?

100
00:05:58,079 --> 00:05:59,040
Let me tell you.

101
00:05:59,480 --> 00:06:00,319
(Termination of Employment Agreement)
You're fired.

102
00:06:00,319 --> 00:06:01,020
(Termination of Employment Agreement)

103
00:06:01,439 --> 00:06:03,600
We don't need

104
00:06:03,680 --> 00:06:04,800
an irresponsible journalist like you.

105
00:06:05,800 --> 00:06:06,360
Editor,

106
00:06:07,759 --> 00:06:08,480
I submitted

107
00:06:08,600 --> 00:06:10,959
a proposal on Meiyan Cosmetics
raw material investigation.

108
00:06:11,319 --> 00:06:13,079
I've been investigating this whole time.

109
00:06:13,560 --> 00:06:14,399
Investigating?

110
00:06:15,120 --> 00:06:17,319
What kind of investigation
takes this long?

111
00:06:18,000 --> 00:06:19,360
You're just coasting

112
00:06:19,959 --> 00:06:21,120
on a few journalism awards

113
00:06:21,839 --> 00:06:23,079
and don't take me seriously.

114
00:06:23,480 --> 00:06:24,199
Get out!

115
00:06:24,519 --> 00:06:26,240
Pack up and go home.

116
00:06:27,120 --> 00:06:27,680
Leave!

117
00:06:28,199 --> 00:06:29,639
Su Li was in an accident.

118
00:06:29,879 --> 00:06:31,360
There's no need to be this harsh.

119
00:06:31,920 --> 00:06:32,560
Zhang Chao!

120
00:06:33,040 --> 00:06:34,519
Do you want to get fired too?

121
00:06:34,759 --> 00:06:35,199
You...

122
00:06:37,160 --> 00:06:38,279
You don't like me, do you?

123
00:06:39,519 --> 00:06:40,120
Guess what,

124
00:06:40,680 --> 00:06:41,360
I don't like you either.

125
00:06:42,839 --> 00:06:44,680
I became a journalist
to uncover the truth

126
00:06:44,800 --> 00:06:45,879
and bring justice to the public.

127
00:06:46,480 --> 00:06:47,720
Even if I leave this place,

128
00:06:49,439 --> 00:06:50,480
I can still investigate.

129
00:06:53,079 --> 00:06:54,000
A journalist, huh?

130
00:06:55,480 --> 00:06:56,399
I'll show you!

131
00:06:57,000 --> 00:06:58,519
Journalist! Journalist!

132
00:06:59,079 --> 00:06:59,480
You!

133
00:07:00,120 --> 00:07:00,879
What kind of journalist are you?

134
00:07:01,000 --> 00:07:01,560
Go home!

135
00:07:04,680 --> 00:07:05,600
Don't do anything crazy!

136
00:07:07,439 --> 00:07:08,439
This is a society of laws.

137
00:07:08,519 --> 00:07:09,360
Don't come any closer!

138
00:07:09,759 --> 00:07:10,199
I'm warning you.

139
00:07:10,360 --> 00:07:11,120
Don't mess with me!

140
00:07:12,279 --> 00:07:13,120
What are you doing?

141
00:07:13,600 --> 00:07:15,040
Su Li, what are you doing?

142
00:07:17,560 --> 00:07:19,519
Great quality wig.

143
00:07:20,360 --> 00:07:22,199
Get a better one next time.

144
00:07:23,079 --> 00:07:23,639
Su Li!

145
00:07:24,120 --> 00:07:25,000
I'm telling you...

146
00:07:26,680 --> 00:07:27,720
You insulted me!

147
00:07:27,800 --> 00:07:28,680
I'll sue you!

148
00:07:29,680 --> 00:07:30,439
My wig!

149
00:07:31,480 --> 00:07:32,199
Su Li!

150
00:07:33,399 --> 00:07:34,360
Just you wait!

151
00:07:35,000 --> 00:07:37,040
No media company will ever hire you!

152
00:07:37,240 --> 00:07:37,480
Su Li!

153
00:07:37,480 --> 00:07:39,279
You'll never be a journalist again!

154
00:07:41,000 --> 00:07:42,319
The editor just got a new car.

155
00:07:42,759 --> 00:07:43,720
I suspect he took a bribe.

156
00:07:44,199 --> 00:07:45,000
He's kept the Meiyan story

157
00:07:45,120 --> 00:07:46,079
tightly under wraps.

158
00:07:47,439 --> 00:07:48,920
This is all He Jinchen's doing.

159
00:07:50,399 --> 00:07:52,680
He thinks throwing money around
to block my journalism career

160
00:07:53,160 --> 00:07:54,120
will force me to give up?

161
00:07:54,319 --> 00:07:55,079
So what will you do?

162
00:07:57,160 --> 00:07:58,160
If he blocks one path,

163
00:07:58,480 --> 00:07:59,800
I will find another.

164
00:08:01,000 --> 00:08:01,759
Let's work together.

165
00:08:02,639 --> 00:08:03,839
I'll be in the open,
you'll be in the shadows.

166
00:08:04,199 --> 00:08:05,279
Let's make a big splash.

167
00:08:14,720 --> 00:08:15,319
Qingmei.

168
00:08:16,839 --> 00:08:18,000
I need to talk to you.

169
00:08:19,000 --> 00:08:19,759
Follow me.

170
00:08:37,759 --> 00:08:39,000
Do you know

171
00:08:40,679 --> 00:08:42,279
how much I've missed you

172
00:08:43,320 --> 00:08:45,159
while you were gone?

173
00:08:46,480 --> 00:08:47,759
I... I...

174
00:08:47,919 --> 00:08:48,879
I didn't...

175
00:08:51,159 --> 00:08:52,039
I didn't...

176
00:08:53,799 --> 00:08:55,519
You avoided me.

177
00:08:56,840 --> 00:08:58,399
You said I was poor,

178
00:08:58,919 --> 00:09:00,759
said I wasn't good enough for you,

179
00:09:04,600 --> 00:09:07,639
and then you married
that good-for-nothing.

180
00:09:09,399 --> 00:09:10,759
But now you know

181
00:09:10,919 --> 00:09:12,600
how much money I've made?

182
00:09:13,679 --> 00:09:15,519
I bought a house ten times
bigger than his.

183
00:09:15,559 --> 00:09:16,399
But you?

184
00:09:16,519 --> 00:09:17,759
One illness, and you are gone.

185
00:09:18,080 --> 00:09:20,000
Do you really dislike me that much?

186
00:09:20,240 --> 00:09:22,200
Do you really not want to see me?

187
00:09:29,200 --> 00:09:29,960
Thank goodness.

188
00:09:32,639 --> 00:09:34,360
Thankfully she had you.

189
00:09:35,120 --> 00:09:36,279
Your personality,

190
00:09:37,120 --> 00:09:38,240
your every smile and gesture

191
00:09:39,639 --> 00:09:41,159
look so much like hers.

192
00:09:46,440 --> 00:09:48,559
From now on, you'll stay
by my side in her place.

193
00:09:49,039 --> 00:09:49,720
Okay?

194
00:09:53,399 --> 00:09:54,279
Okay.

195
00:09:56,000 --> 00:09:57,279
Yes, I promise you.

196
00:09:58,519 --> 00:09:59,720
I'll stay

197
00:10:01,200 --> 00:10:02,759
and keep you company in Mom's place.

198
00:10:08,440 --> 00:10:09,519
That dress...

199
00:10:10,679 --> 00:10:11,600
Didn't you say

200
00:10:12,320 --> 00:10:14,519
it was Mom's favorite?

201
00:10:15,679 --> 00:10:17,799
You said she loved wearing it
when she went to the library.

202
00:10:22,639 --> 00:10:23,679
I'll put it on

203
00:10:25,080 --> 00:10:25,960
and show you.

204
00:10:27,240 --> 00:10:27,840
Okay?

205
00:11:36,279 --> 00:11:37,440
Do you remember?

206
00:11:39,080 --> 00:11:40,120
It was raining that day.

207
00:11:41,080 --> 00:11:42,480
You didn't have an umbrella.

208
00:11:43,840 --> 00:11:45,279
I gave you mine

209
00:11:46,919 --> 00:11:48,759
and ran into the rain myself.

210
00:11:50,480 --> 00:11:51,240
That day,

211
00:11:53,200 --> 00:11:54,919
I should have walked with you.

212
00:11:58,799 --> 00:12:00,200
I regret it, actually.

213
00:12:02,200 --> 00:12:03,440
I shouldn't have let you get wet.

214
00:12:22,960 --> 00:12:23,759
Go back to your room.

215
00:12:24,240 --> 00:12:24,759
Remember,

216
00:12:25,360 --> 00:12:26,200
just like before,

217
00:12:26,840 --> 00:12:28,759
what happens here stays here.

218
00:12:32,080 --> 00:12:32,919
Rest assured.

219
00:12:34,399 --> 00:12:35,519
I won't tell anyone.

220
00:13:34,140 --> 00:13:38,900
♪Time stole the proof of our love♪

221
00:13:38,900 --> 00:13:43,740
♪Hidden in the moonlight,
lost in the clouds♪

222
00:13:43,740 --> 00:13:48,300
♪Tangled glances and love fall together♪

223
00:13:48,300 --> 00:13:53,220
♪Into a spiral of thoughts,
memories rewinding♪

224
00:13:53,220 --> 00:13:57,020
♪Feelings both strange and familiar♪

225
00:13:57,020 --> 00:14:01,820
♪I just know you're
where my heart belongs♪

226
00:14:01,820 --> 00:14:04,660
♪Can't remember
when this flutter started♪

227
00:14:04,660 --> 00:14:07,340
♪Or how it's supposed to end♪

228
00:14:07,700 --> 00:14:13,260
♪Goodbye to the world rushing in♪

229
00:14:13,660 --> 00:14:20,460
♪Let me hide in your eyes
and never leave♪

230
00:14:20,740 --> 00:14:25,420
♪Feel the rhythm of your heartbeat♪

231
00:14:25,580 --> 00:14:32,380
♪Every tomorrow seems worth the wait♪

232
00:14:32,700 --> 00:14:39,500
♪Let me fill the emptiness of a century♪

233
00:14:39,700 --> 00:14:44,180
♪As the wind brushes past your hem♪

234
00:14:44,180 --> 00:14:47,540
♪All my hidden feelings come undone♪

235
00:14:47,540 --> 00:14:54,460
♪Right as I confess my love♪
